85 health fields who commit to rural practice; and
86 (2) Loan repayment for licensed providers who work in
87 rural areas for at least two years.
88 (b) Funds may be used for tuition, licensure fees, and
89 relocation costs.
90 Section 8. The department shall adopt rules necessary
91 to implement, administer, and facilitate this act.
92 Section 9. This act shall become effective on October
93 1, 2026.
